The paper discusses experiments comparing the performance of different visual cues in estimating part-to-whole charts, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of Amazon's Mechanical Turk service also suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses the controversy surrounding pie charts, which could be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of visual cues and comparisons between different chart types could also relate to computer vision (cs.CV).
